SIMPLE: demurely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demurely
<hw>De*mure"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a demure manner; soberly;
gravely; -- now, commonly, with a mere show of gravity or
modesty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They . . . looked as <qex>demurely</qex> as they could; for 't was
a hanging matter to laugh unseasonably.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 390 --></p>

<p><ent>Demureness</ent>⟦br⟧
